<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Chelsea striker Olivier Giroud has emerged as a potential target for Juventus.</p>

<p>The Italians champions agreed to release Gonzalo Higuain on Thursday but are struggling to reach agreement with Luis Suarez of Barcelona or their alternative Edin Dzeko of Roma.</p>

<p>Juventus have also considered a return for Everton's Moise Kean but Giroud brings experience and a proven goal scoring record.</p>

<p>Chelsea striker Olivier Giroud has emerged as a potential target for Juventus</p>

<p>Though no offer has been made, he is on Juve's list of options as they strive to add a striker over the next few days.</p>

<p>Giroud, 33, scored his 40th international goal for France this week. </p>

<p>He signed a new contract at Chelsea earlier this year after seeing potential moves to Inter Milan and Lazio fall through. </p>

<p>The Serie A champions are struggling to reach agreement with Luis Suarez of Barcelona</p>
